 poetry.Edward FitzGerald's translation of the Rubáiyát of Omar Khayyám has been one of the world's most popular books. Since the first version in 1859, new editions, reprints and translations have appeared in an almost endless flow, varying from plain text to highly decorated, illustrated editions and from almost microscopic miniatures to monumental, oversized volumes. FitzGerald's translation stands out, but there are hundreds of other translations, from many countries, and you will find them all in this book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aLIT. 4aLanguage and Literature. 4aLiterary Theory, Criticism, and History. 4aMiddle East. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh  aOmar Khayyám, The Rubáiyát, Bibliography, Persia.1 aSeyed-Gohrab, Asghar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102378640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978940060008940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789400600089423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789400600089/original  a978-3-11-102378-6  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK